title: Weaver's Thesis Book (France), 1895
description: Large notebook as prepared by a student of weaving at Lyon with samples, graphs, descriptions of weave process. Silks in various basic weaves. Contain one-hundred thirty pages and eighty samples.

tombstone.epitaph: Weaver's Thesis Book (France), 1895; cloth, paper, silk; H x W: 39 × 27 cm (15 3/8 × 10 5/8 in.); 1961-129-4
